'''''Assédio''''' ({{literal translation}}: ''Harassment'') is a Brazilian [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] [[web television]] series produced by [[Rede Globo]] and O2 Filmes that premiered on the streaming service Globoplay on September 21, 2018. Based on the book ''“A Clínica – A Farsa e os Crimes de Roger Abdelmassih”'' by Vicente Vilardaga about the former Brazilian physician [[Roger Abdelmassih]], is written by Maria Camargo and directed by Amora Mautner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/noticia-da-tv/2018/09/conheca-a-historia-e-os-personagens-da-serie-assedio|title='Assédio' estreia no Globoplay com história de Roger Abdelmassih e relatos de abusos sexuais |language=Portuguese |date=September 17, 2018|website=observatoriodatelevisao}}</ref>
==Premise== Dr. Roger Sadala is a famous and trendy physician specializing in artificial insemination. A professional above any suspicion, responsible for the birth of thousands of babies.
Dozens of women entered his clinic with the dream of being mothers, and during the procedure, they were drugged and raped by the doctor. By discovering the various cases, these women unite by pain and decide to join forces to denounce the doctor and put him to prison. And during that time, it is discovered that in addition to sexual crimes, the physician used a somewhat unorthodox methods in his reproductive processes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/2018/09/20/assedio-estreia-no-globoplay-com-historia-de-roger-abdelmassih-e-relatos-de-abusos-sexuais.ghtml|title=Conheça a história e os personagens da série Assédio |language=Portuguese |date=September 20, 2018|website=G1}}</ref>
