{{Infobox NRHP | name = Gates Hall and Pultneyville Public Square | nrhp_type = | image = Gates Hall Sept 10.jpg | caption = Gates Hall, September 2010 | location= Lake Rd., [[Pultneyville, New York]] | coordinates = {{coord|43|16|48|N|77|11|13|W|region:US_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = New York#USA | built = 1826 | architect = Cornwall, Andrew; Cornwall, Ansel | architecture = Greek Revival, Queen Anne | added = March 03, 2000 | area = {{convert|2|acre}} | governing_body = Private | refnum = 00000177<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> }} '''Gates Hall and Pultneyville Public Square''' is a historic [[theater]] and [[village green]] located at [[Pultneyville, New York|Pultneyville]] in [[Wayne County, New York]]. Gates Hall was built in 1826 by the Union Church Society as a place of worship for the community's Methodists, Presbyterians, and Episcopalians. In 1867, the building began to be used as a theater. It was remodeled in 1894 in the [[Queen Anne style architecture in the United States|Queen Anne]] style to serve as a multipurpose civic building. It is a two-story, gable roofed building resting on a raised basement. Pultneyville Public Square is a village green, approximately one acre in extent, that serves the passive recreational needs of the hamlet.<ref name="nrhpinv_ny">{{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=10153|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Gates Hall and Pultneyville Public Square|date=December 1999|accessdate=2009-11-10 |author=Nancy L. Todd|publisher=[[New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation]]}}''See also:'' {{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=10145|title=Accompanying photo}}</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2000.<ref name="nris"/>
